0National%20Rally%20(RN)%2C%20led%20by%20Marine%20Le%20Pen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20end%2C%20it%20passed%20through%20the%20lower%20house%20with%20votes%20from%20Macron%E2%80%99s%20centrist%20coalition%20and%20conservative%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterior%20Minister%20Gerald%20Darmanin%20%E2%80%94%20who%20had%20spearheaded%20the%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20expressed%20relief%20after%20a%20large%20majority%20voted%20in%20favour%2C%20meaning%20it%20no%20longer%20depended%20on%20the%20support%20from%20those%20far-right%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20subject%20of%20immigration%20is%20a%20major%20political%20plank%20for%20the%20upcoming%20parliamentary%20elections.%20While%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20bill%20would%20have%20favoured%20Macron%2C%20the%20support%20shown%20by%20Le%20Pen%20%E2%80%94%20who%20called%20the%20stricter%20bill%20%E2%80%9Ca%20great%20ideological%20victory%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20far-right%20%E2%80%94%20can%20also%20improve%20her%20chances%20in%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20the%20new%20immigration%20law%20entail%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20the%20bill%20was%20first%20submitted%2C%20it%20has%20seen%20various%20amendments%20toughening%20the%20immigration%20rules%2C%20with%20the%20left%20accusing%20the%20government%20of%20giving%20in%20to%20the%20pressure%20from%20the%20far-right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20legislation%20more%20agreeable%20for%20the%20right%2C%20the%20government%20decided%20to%20weaken%20measures%20that%20would%20have%20allowed%20some%20immigrants%20residency%20permits.%20The%20government%20also%20agreed%20to%20extend%20the%20duration%20of%20stay%20in%20France%20for%20migrants%20to%20be%20eligible%20to%20access%20welfare%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20new%20legislation%2C%20access%20to%20housing%20benefits%20will%20be%20also%20be%20delayed%20for%20unemployed%20non-EU%20migrants%20by%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20gain%20the%20support%20of%20the%20right%2C%20the%20government%20has%20also%20introduced%20migration%20quotas%20which%20will%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20immigrants%E2%80%99%20children%20to%20become%20French.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20now%20it%20will%20be%20easier%20for%20migrants%20working%20in%20sectors%20that%20lack%20labour%20to%20get%20a%20residency%20permit%2C%20it%20will%20also%20be%20easier%20to%20expel%20illegal%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ffrance-passes-controversial-immigration-bill%2Fa-67772998%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703050809000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20110131%2FGA0_RMiWIAA5UR0.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpanders-to-rightwing-france-passes-new-strict-immigration-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bill%20aimed%20at%20tightening%20immigration%20rules%20was%20passed%20without%20the%20need%20for%20far-right%20votes%2C%20despite%20major%20opposition.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpanders-to-rightwing-france-passes-new-strict-immigration-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Descendants%20fight%20to%20maintain%20historic%20Black%20communities.%20Keeping%20their%20legacy%20alive%20is%20complicated%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703050718000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106145044%2Cimgsize-1184234.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdescendants-fight-to-maintain-historic-black-communities-keeping-their-legacy-alive-is-complicated%2Farticleshow%2F106143950.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesof