0Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20ruled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-rules-trump-disqualified-from-2024-primary-ballot-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%20ineligible%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20run%20for%20or%20hold%20public%20office%20in%20the%20state%20due%20to%20his%20role%20in%20the%20January%206%20attack%20on%20the%20Capitol%2C%20the%20former%20president%20vowed%20to%20appeal%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20qualification%20for%20office%20will%20likely%20be%20handed%20off%20to%20the%20highest%20court%20in%20the%20land.%20While%20the%20Colorado%20decision%20has%20focused%20on%20his%20eligibility%20to%20be%20included%20on%20the%20state's%20primary%20ballot%2C%20the%20ruling%20would%20also%20apply%20to%20the%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20legal%20experts%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider%20the%20options%20that%20SCOTUS%20has%3A%20do%20nothing%20and%20allow%20Colorado's%20ruling%20to%20lapse%2C%20refuse%20to%20add%20the%20case%20to%20the%20docket%2C%20or%20agree%20to%20hear%20arguments%20and%20issue%20a%20decision%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20justices%20are%20on%20something%20of%20a%20time%20limit%20to%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20ruling%2C%20the%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20wrote%20that%20unless%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESCOTUS%20chooses%20to%20review%20the%20case%20before%20January%204%2C%202024%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20day%20before%20the%20deadline%20to%20certify%20the%20state's%20presidential%20primary%20ballot%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20Trump's%20name%20will%20be%20added%20to%20the%20ballot%20until%20the%20high%20court%20hands%20down%20a%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20or%20his%20lawyers%3C%2Fa%3E%20ask%20SCOTUS%20to%20review%20the%20ruling%20before%20January%204%2C%20he%20will%20be%20on%20the%20ballot%2C%20Doron%20Kalir%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Cleveland-Marshall%20College%20of%20Law%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20And%20while%20SCOTUS%20will%20have%20to%20decide%20whether%20they'll%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20they%20will%20not%20have%20to%20weigh%20in%20and%20make%20a%20final%20ruling%20before%20that%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20as%20we%20sit%20here%20right%20now%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20still%20able%20to%20be%20listed%20on%20the%20Republican%20primary%20ballot%20in%20Colorado%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Becker%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Election%20Innovation%20and%20Research%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BOnly%20if%20the%20United%20States%20Supreme%20Court%20declined%20to%20take%20the%20case%20or%20otherwise%20upholds%20the%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20will%20his%20name%20be%20removed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20waits%20out%20the%20clock%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESCOTUS%20could%20decide%20to%20wait%20to%20hear%20this%20case%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20former%20Assistant%20US%20Attorney%20Kevin%20O'Brien%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20may%20not%20be%20the%20right%20vehicle%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-smith-trump-immunity-claim-supreme-court-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20wants%20to%20have%20to%20rule%20on%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20or%20section%20three%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20in%20particular%3B%20they%20may%20want%20a%20different%20case%2C%20they%20may%20want%20several%20cases%2C%20they%20may%20wait%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20know%2C%20the%20pressure%20of%20time%20is%20upon%20them.%20So%20that%20would%20argue%20for%20taking%20this%20case%20soon%20and%20getting%20it%20argued%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Lemieux%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20and%20an%20expert%20in%20constitutional%20law%2C%20said%20it's%20possible%20SCOTUS%20could%20take%20up%20the%20case%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-courts-shadow-docket-poses-institutional-ethics-concerns-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshadow%20docket%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20issue%20a%20stay%20of%20its%20own%20without%20making%20a%20formal%20ruling.%20Doing%20so%20would%20prevent%20the%20Colorado%20decision%20from%20going%20into%20effect%20while%20the%20appeals%20process%20plays%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20other%20experts%20think%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20most%20inclined%20to%20try%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20the%20decision%20directly%2C%20given%20the%20time-sensitive%20nature%20of%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAt%20issue%3A%20the%20insurrection%20clause%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20its%20decision%2C%20cited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-14th-amendment-could-prevent-trump-from-office-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esection%203%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20insurrection%20clause%2C%20which%20specifies%20that%20officials%20who%20have%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20in%20insurrection%20or%20rebellion%26quot%3B%20or%20have%20%26quot%3Bgiven%20aid%20or%20comfort%26quot%3B%20to%20those%20carrying%20out%20an%20insurrection%20are%20ineligible%20to%20run%20for%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotre%20Dame%20Law%20School%20professor%20Derek%20Muller%2C%20an%20election%20law%20scholar%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20believes%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20be%20inclined%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20because%20it%20deals%20with%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20never%20been%20subject%20to%20interpretation%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20150%20years%20it%20has%20been%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20explicitly%20names%20senators%20and%20representatives%20in%20Congress%2C%20the%20electors%20of%20the%20President%20and%20Vice-President%2C%20and%20any%20official%20holding%20%26quot%3Bany%20office%2C%20civil%20or%20military%2C%20under%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20as%20accountable%20to%20the%20rule.%20But%20it%20doesn't%20specifically%20mention%20the%20presidency.%20And%20while%20the%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20determined%20the%20presidency%20is%20included%20in%20the%20provision%2C%20SCOTUS%20could%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20current%20ruling%20only%20applies%20to%20Colorado%2C%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20state's%20decision%20could%20encourage%20groups%20in%20other%20states%20to%20file%20similar%20lawsuits%20in%20hopes%20of%20kicking%20Trump%20off%20the%20ballot.%20While%20losing%20Colorado%2C%20which%20leans%20blue%2C%20would%20not%20be%20a%20significant%20disadvantage%20to%20Trump%20in%20a%20general%20election%2C%20the%20consequences%20would%20be%20more%20significant%20if%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-should-worry-about-swing-state-suburbs-in-2020-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswing%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%20challenged%20his%20qualifications%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExcluding%20a%20leading%20presidential%20candidate%20and%20former%20president%20from%20the%20ballot%20is%20a%20major%20decision%2C%20and%20I'm%20just%20not%20sure%20that%20the%20court%20can%20stand%20by%20not%20doing%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Muller%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20have%20to%20weigh%20in.%20But%20how%20it's%20going%20to%20resolve%20the%20case%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%20There's%20lots%20of%20different%20ways%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecan%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20SCOTUS%20takes%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ends-affirmative-action-colleges-decision-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20decides%20not%20to%20take%20the%20Colorado%20case%2C%20it%20will%20effectively%20kick%20the%20issue%20back%20to%20individual%20states%2C%20allowing%20each%20one%20to%20determine%20whether%20Trump%20is%20eligible%20to%20be%20named%20on%20their%20ballots.%20But%2C%20if%20SCOTUS%20agrees%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20as%20many%20experts%20believe%20they%20will%2C%20there's%20no%20clear-cut%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20can%20reverse%20this%20case%20on%20no%20less%20than%205%20or%206%20grounds%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalir%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20reasons%20SCOTUS%20could%20overturn%20the%20case%20vary%20widely%20and%20include%20issues%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20and%20the%20limited%20powers%20of%20state%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKalir%20said%20SCOTUS%20could%20also%20decide%20that%20due%20process%20is%20required%20to%20determine%20a%20person%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%20to%20use%20the%2014th%20Amendment%2C%20as%20a%20dissenting%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20argued%2C%20and%20may%20determine%20that%20Trump%20is%20eligible%20to%20be%20on%20the%20ballot%20until%20he%20is%20convicted%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-january-6-criminal-indictment-charges-explained-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrime%20related%20to%20January%206%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristian%20Grose%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20and%20public%20policy%20at%20USC%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20though%20it's%20unlikely%2C%20it's%20certainly%20possible%20SCOTUS%20could%20surprise%20everyone%20and%20agree%20with%20the%20Colorado%20ruling%2C%20ultimately%20banning%20Trump%20from%20being%20on%20the%20ballot%20not%20just%20in%20that%20state%2C%20but%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20could%20actually%20roll%20in%20agreement%20with%20Colorado%20and%20if%20they%20do%2C%20that%20would%20bar%20him%20from%20the%20ballot%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Grose%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20a%20bit%20of%20risk%2C%20even%20though%20three%20of%20the%20people%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-conservative-majority-could-reshape-american-elections-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappointed%20by%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20might%20be%20more%20aligned%20with%20Trump%2C%20you%20know%2C%20it's%20still%20a%20risk%20to%20have%20to%20take%20something%20like%20this%20to%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20outcomes%20in%20the%20case%20run%20the%20gamut%20from%20Trump's%20Supreme%20Court-ordered%20vindication%20to%20the%20possibility%20that%20he%20could%20be%20permanently%20banned%20from%20office%20by%20the%20highest%20court%20in%20the%20land.%20And%20we'll%20have%20to%20wait%20a%20bit%20longer%20to%20see%20what%20they%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20of%20those%20things%20where%20you're%20involved%20no%20matter%20what%20you%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20abstain%2C%20you're%20involved.%20If%20you%20rule%20in%20favor%20of%20Trump%2C%20you're%20involved%2C%20and%20if%20you%20uphold%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Colorado%20did%2C%20you're%20also%20interfering%20and%20involved%20so%2C%20you%20know%2C%20there's%20no%20easy%20out%20for%20that.%20They're%20gonna%20have%20to%20think%20long%20and%20hard%20about%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-to-determine-if-trump-can-run-president-again-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%