20by%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal%20Party%20MP%20Jayant%20Chaudhary%2C%20Union%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20finance%20Bhagwat%20Karad%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6out%20of%20approximately%2051.11%20crore%20PMJDY%20accounts%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cnaround%2020%25%20accounts%20are%20inoperative%20as%20on%2006.12.2023.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20what%20constitutes%20an%20inoperative%20account%2C%20Karad%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20guidelines%2C%20a%20savings%20as%20well%20as%20current%20account%20should%20be%20treated%20as%20inoperative%2F%20dormant%2C%20if%20there%20are%20no%20customer%20induced%20transactions%20in%20the%20account%20for%20over%20a%20period%20of%20two%20years.%20The%20reasons%20for%20the%20account%20turning%20inoperative%20can%20be%20many%20and%20it%20has%20no%20direct%20co-relation%20to%20the%20account-holder%20being%20untraceable.%20Further%2C%20the%20customers%20at%20any%20point%20of%20time%20can%20make%20a%20request%20for%20activation%20of%20inoperative%20account%20without%20being%20charged.%20The%20banks%20make%20these%20accounts%20operative%20after%20performing%20necessary%20Know%20Your%20Customer%20(KYC).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20little%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20inoperative%20accounts%20belong%20to%20women%2C%20the%20minister%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20on%2006.12.2023%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%2010.34%20crore%20inoperative%20PMJDY%20accounts%2C%204.93%20crore%20accounts%20belong%20to%20women.%20The%20deposited%20balance%20in%20the%20inoperative%20PMJDY%20accounts%20is%20around%20Rs.12%2C779%20crore%20which%20is%20around%206.12%25%20of%20the%20total%20deposited%20balance%20in%20PMJDY%20accounts.%20This%20balance%20continues%20to%20earn%20interest%20at%20par%20with%20that%20applicable%20to%20the%20operative%20accounts%20and%20can%20be%20claimed%20and%20withdrawn%20by%20the%20depositors%20at%20any%20point%20of%20time%20after%20the%20account%20becomes%20operative%20again.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChaudhary%20claimed%20that%20banks%20have%20been%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20reduce%20the%20percentage%20of%20inoperative%20accounts%2C%20including%20through%20awareness%20campaigns%2C%20and%20so%20the%20percentage%20of%20inoperative%20accounts%20has%20come%20down%20from%2040%25%20in%20March%202017%20to%2020%25%20in%20November%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jan%20Dhan%20Yojana%2C%20a%20pet%20project%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20in%20his%20first%20term%2C%20was%20launched%20in%202014%20and%20pushed%20the%20idea%20of%20financial%20inclusion%20through%20opening%20zero-balance%20accounts.%20However%2C%20multiple%20reports%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20this%20push%20revealed%20that%20simply%20opening%20an%20account%20did%20not%20mean%20people%20would%20use%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703047252000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F20-of-banks-accounts-opened-under-jan-dhan-yojana-are-inoperative-finance-ministry%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20little%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20inoperative%20accounts%20belong%20to%20women.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F20-of-banks-accounts-opened-under-jan-dhan-yojana-are-inoperative-finance-ministry%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Yorkers%20leaving%20the%20city%20had%20median%20earnings%20of%20%2449%2C000%20as%20life%20in%20NYC%20becomes%20ever%20more%20of%20a%20financial%20pipe%20dream%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20York%20City%20skyline%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65824b991c5c7b8c9a0a1b0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20New%20York%20City%20skyline%3Cp%3ECHARLY%20TRIBALLEAU%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20population%20of%20New%20York%20City%20has%20fallen%20since%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20are%20being%20priced%20out%2C%20with%20the%20median%20wage%20of%20those%20leaving%20in%202022%20lower%20than%20the%20year%20before.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20only%20demographic%20group%20analyzed%20by%20the%20city%20which%20had%20grown%20since%202020%20was%20seniors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20City's%20population%20has%20plummeted%20by%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20between%202020%20and%202022%20%E2%80%94%20shrinking%20over%205%25%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osc.ny.gov%2Fpress%2Freleases%2F2023%2F12%2Fchanging-face-post-pandemic-new-york-city%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20state%20comptroller%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPart%20of%20this%20stems%20from%20New%20Yorkers%20being%20priced%20out%20of%20the%20city.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20median%20wage%20of%20those%20leaving%20the%20city%20fell%20to%20%2449%2C000%2C%20an%2018%25%20decrease%20from%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20newcomers%20to%20the%20city%20had%20a%20median%20wage%20of%20%2451%2C000%20in%202022.%20This%20marked%20a%2013%25%20increase%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20context%2C%20the%20national%20median%20wage%20of%20workers%20in%202022%20was%20%2446%2C310%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes_nat.htm%2300-0000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20City's%20demographic%20makeup%20is%20also%20changing%2C%20with%20the%20report%20finding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20city's%20populace%20is%20overall%20older%20and%20wealthier%2C%20with%20a%20rebounding%20population%20of%20international%20migrants%20and%20declining%20shares%20of%20White%20and%20Black%20New%20Yorkers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20demographic%20group%20analyzed%20by%20the%20city%20that%20saw%20growth%20from%202020%20to%202022%20was%20seniors%2C%20which%20increased%20by%203.3%25.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20population%20of%20under-18s%20fell%20by%207.5%25%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20pandemic's%20wake%2C%20we%20see%20an%20altered%20population%2C%20and%20it%20raises%20longstanding%20concerns%20about%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20the%20growing%20wealth%20gap%2C%20the%20need%20to%20preserve%20a%20strong%20middle%20class%2C%20and%20the%20challenges%20of%20serving%20an%20aging%20population%2C%20while%20ensuring%20that%20families%20are%20able%20to%20raise%20their%20children%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20state%20comptroller%20Thomas%20DiNapoli.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIssues%20of%20affordability%20have%20long%20plagued%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-of-nyc-residents-cant-afford-housing-food-healthcare-report-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20City%20True%20Cost%20of%20Living%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20report%2C%20published%20in%20April%2C%20found%20that%20half%20of%20the%20city's%20working-age%20households%20earn%20less%20than%20the%20%24100%2C000%20necessary%20to%20meet%20their%20basic%20needs.%20That%20amounts%20to%20nearly%203%20million%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lack%20of%20affordable%20housing%20led%20the%20city%20to%20unveil%20a%20pilot%20program%20in%20November%2C%20offering%20homeowners%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-funding-adu-tiny-homehousing-shortage-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eup%20to%20%24395%2C000%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20build%20an%20extra%20dwelling%20in%20their%20homes.%20The%20effort%20is%20part%20of%20the%20city's%20new%20housing%20reforms%2C%20which%20aim%20to%20build%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-real-estate-prices-housing-apartments-eric-adams-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E100%2C000%20new%20homes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20leading%20the%20charge%20out%20of%20increasingly%20unaffordable%20cities%20tended%20to%20be%20millennial%20homebuyers%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2021-home-buyers-and-sellers-generational-trends-03-16-2021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20however%2C%20many%20of%20those%20who%20left%20have%20found%20themselves%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-regretting-moves-from-city-to-suburbs-housing-crisis-millennials-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eregretting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20trading%20in%20expensive%20city%20apartments%20close%20to%20friends%20for%20a%20lonelier%20life%20out%20in%20the%20suburbs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-wage-people-leaving-nyc-financial-pipe-dream-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703046863000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65825164a79e5746976b5e6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-wage-people-leaving-nyc-financial-pipe-dream-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20city's%20demographic%20makeup%20is%20also%20changing%2C%20with%20the%20report%20stating%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20city's%20populace%20is%20overall%20older%20and%20wealthier.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kteo%40insider.com%20(Kai%20Xiang%20Teo)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-wage-people-leaving-nyc-financial-pipe-dream-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20093656%2Ftablet-314153_1280.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%202023%20that%20has%20been%20introduced%20in%20parliament%20this%20session%20is%20an%20extremely%20draconian%20law.%20It%20forces%20government%20control%20on%20every%20message%20that%20is%20being%20transmitted%2C%20emitted%20or%20received%20in%20any%20form%20including%20wired%2C%20electronic%2C%20optical%20etc.%20The%20definition%20of%20a%20message%20in%20the%20Bill%20is%20very%20broad%20with%20inclusion%20of%20sign%2C%20signal%2C%20writing%2C%20text%2C%20image%2C%20sound%2C%20video%2C%20data%20stream%2C%20intelligence%20or%20information%20sent%20through%20telecommunication.%20This%20is%20so%20vast%20that%20every%20internet%2Fdigital%20app%20within%20the%20boundaries%20of%20India%20has%20to%20comply%20under%20the%20upcoming%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20is%20creating%20a%20new%20authorisation%20regime%2C%20where%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20would%20have%20to%20apply%20for%20authorisation%20to%20operate%20in%20India.%20With%20the%20wide%20definition%20of%20telecommunication%20and%20messages%2C%20this%20will%20ideally%20be%20applicable%20to%20every%20social%20media%20application%20out%20there%20%E2%80%93%20WhatsApp%2C%20Facebook%2C%20X%2C%20Instagram%2C%20etc.%20This%20Bill%20essentially%20brings%20a%20licence%20regime%20to%20the%20internet.%20Services%20not%20complying%20with%20the%20law%20could%20be%20likely%20to%20be%20blocked%20or%20banned%20in%20India%2C%20like%20TikTok%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20347px)%2085vw%2C%20347px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22347%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo-300x209.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-637305%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22242%5C%22%3EThe%20Internet%20and%20Mobile%20Association%20of%20India%2C%20a%20leading%20industry%20body%20of%20internet%20companies%20and%20startups%20in%20the%20country%2C%20has%20welcomed%20the%20Bill%20for%20removing%20over-the-top%20platforms%20(OTTs)%20from%20being%20regulated.%20But%20this%20is%20probably%20a%20false%20sense%20of%20celebration%2C%20as%20this%20Bill%20will%20have%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20every%20internet%20company%20with%20the%20authorisation%20regime%20and%20the%20compliance%20requirements%20under%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%202023%20will%20replace%20colonial%20laws%20of%20the%20Indian%20Telegraph%20Act%201885%20and%20Indian%20Wireless%20Telegraphy%20Act%201933.%20These%20colonial%20laws%20provided%20extreme%20forms%20of%20control%20over%20communications%20in%20colonial%20India%20to%20the%20British.%20While%20the%20Bill%20is%20being%20praised%20by%20the%20telecom%20industry%20for%20replacing%20archaic%20colonial%20laws%2C%20the%20Telecommunication%20Bill%202023%20is%20expected%20to%20provide%20a%20larger%20control%20than%20these%20colonial%20laws%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20its%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20or%20a%20state%20government%20to%20take%20over%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20network%20in%20the%20event%20of%20public%20emergency%20or%20safety.%20It%20allows%20officials%20of%20both%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20intercept%20or%20detain%20or%20not%20to%20transmit%20messages%20from%20a%20single%20person%20or%20class%20of%20persons.%20This%20single%20measure%20gives%20officials%20immense%20powers%20to%20control%20and%20spy%20on%20every%20message%20over%20the%20entire%20telecom%20network%20for%20public%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20further%20mandates%20biometric%20verification%20of%20every%20social%20media%20user%20by%20the%20telecommunication%20services.%20This%20forces%20identification%20for%20all%20forms%20of%20communications%20and%20pushes%20India%E2%80%99s%20KYC%20regime%20across%20the%20internet.%20To%20illustrate%20the%20power%20of%20these%20provisions%2C%20think%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20trying%20to%20access%20all%20the%20details%20of%20every%20individual%20tweeting%20during%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protest%2C%20to%20stop%20every%20message%20with%20a%20certain%20hashtag%20or%20keyword%20or%20to%20block%20people%20from%20accessing%20their%20own%20accounts.%20Every%20aspect%20of%20this%20Bill%20allows%20the%20police%20or%20intelligence%20agencies%20to%20continuously%20monitor%20the%20opposition%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20farmers%E2%80%99%20leaders%20or%20students%20who%20might%20be%20protesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Bill%20provides%20exemptions%20for%20accredited%20media%20professionals%20to%20not%20be%20intercepted%20or%20detained%2C%20it%20would%20require%20every%20journalist%20to%20identify%20themselves%20as%20such%20with%20the%20telecom%20service%20companies.%20Journalists%20would%20have%20to%20register%20with%20every%20telecom%20service%20provider%20including%20social%20media%20and%20other%20communication%20services.%20But%20this%20may%20not%20necessarily%20provide%20them%20with%20the%20media%20freedoms%20and%20privacy%20that%20are%20required%20in%20a%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20KYC%20for%20internet%20apps%20and%20services%20began%20with%20the%20CERT-In%20rules%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fwith-vpn-order-the-government-shows-itll-leave-virtually-nothing-private%5C%22%3Emandating%20KYC%20and%20logging%20for%20VPN%20companies%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%20this%20architecture%20of%20an%20identity-linked%20internet%20telecommunication%20service%20will%20kill%20anonymity%20online.%20This%20in%20itself%20is%20not%20against%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%20Vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20judgment%20recognises%20exemptions%20for%20national%20security%20and%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20grant%20Indians%20the%20right%20of%20anonymity.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20no%20conducive%20environment%20to%20even%20challenge%20these%20upcoming%20surveillance%20laws%20in%20courts%2C%20with%20a%20majoritarian%20executive%20that%20is%20able%20to%20force%20these%20laws%20without%20any%20obstacles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20includes%20all%20these%20provisions%20for%20detention%20of%20messages%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20avoid%20internet%20shutdowns%20and%20look%20for%20alternate%20mechanisms%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20Information%20Technology.%20The%20issue%20of%20access%20to%20internet%20is%20the%20core%20of%20telecommunications%20infrastructure.%20To%20address%20issues%20of%20access%20to%20remote%20areas%2C%20satellite%20based%20internet%20was%20been%20explored%20as%20an%20alternative.%20The%20spectrum%20allocation%20for%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20controversial%2C%20with%20the%20need%20for%20auctions%20vs%20administrative%20allocation%20for%20limited%20scenarios.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20on%20spectrum%20allocation%20would%20be%20revisited.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20note%2C%20spectrum%20allocation%20using%20administrative%20approvals%20alone%20could%20lead%20to%20illegal%20allocations%20and%20scams%20without%20due%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20are%20provisions%20merely%20provided%20for%20public%20safety%2C%20the%20national%20security%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20suspend%2C%20remove%20or%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20specified%20telecommunication%20equipment%20and%20telecommunication%20services%20from%20countries%20or%20persons%20as%20may%20be%20notified.%20So%20like%20TikTok%20being%20banned%2C%20similar%20communication%20and%20media%20applications%20can%20be%20blocked%20from%20countries%20or%20individuals%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20security%20provisions%20also%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20dictate%20telecom%20standards%20for%20equipment%20and%20services%20including%2C%20encryption%2C%20cybersecurity%20and%20data%20processing%20in%20communication.%20The%20security%20standards%20for%20telecommunications%20equipment%20are%20indeed%20important%20and%20can%20be%20detrimental%20to%20national%20security%20if%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20no%20control%20over%20them.%20This%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20with%20the%20geopolitical%20controversies%20across%20the%20world%20of%20not%20allowing%20Chinese%20companies%20like%20Huawei%20and%20ZTE%20to%20build%205G%20infrastructure.%20India%20too%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20any%20Chinese%20equipment%20as%20part%20of%20its%20telecommunications%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20encryption%20standards%20for%20telecommunication%20services%20being%20set%20by%20the%20government%20could%20be%20dangerous%2C%20given%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20interest%20to%20break%20up%20encryption%20of%20WhatsApp%20and%20Signal%20messengers.%20Most%20internet%20communication%20is%20encrypted%20and%20is%20increasingly%20being%20pushed%20towards%20encryption%2C%20to%20evade%20nation%20state%20surveillance%20programmes.%20Meta%20has%20recently%20moved%20all%20of%20its%20messaging%20services%20from%20Facebook%20Messenger%20and%20Instagram%20to%20end-to-end%20encryption%2C%20using%20the%20Signal%20protocol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20with%20censorship%20and%20surveillance%20is%20to%20push%20for%20identification%20and%20control%20of%20communication%20networks.%20As%20the%20saying%20goes%2C%20there%20is%20freedom%20of%20speech%20in%20India%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20guarantee%20of%20freedom%20after%20speech.%20India%E2%80%99s%20censorship%20strategy%20is%20to%20shut%20people%20down%20by%20punishing%20a%20few%20outspoken%20and%20hoping%20the%20rest%20fall%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%20demands%20a%20Chinese-style%20banning%20of%20messages%20based%20on%20keywords%20or%20other%20characteristics.%20Its%20usage%2C%20though%2C%20will%20be%20limited%20to%20scenarios%20like%20the%20case%20of%20a%20public%20emergency%20such%20as%20protests%20and%20riots%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20continuous%20censorship%20that%20exists%20in%20China.%20While%20this%20difference%20might%20exist%2C%20it%20still%20lays%20the%20ground%20for%20a%20larger%20totalitarian%20control%20if%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20eventually%20assert%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%20is%20rapidly%20digitising.%20There%20are%20good%20things%20and%20bad%2C%20speed-bumps%20on%20the%20way%20and%20caveats%20to%20be%20mindful%20of.%20The%20weekly%20column%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3ETerminal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0focuses%20on%20all%20that%20is%20connected%20and%20is%20not%20%E2%80%93%20on%20digital%20issues%2C%20policy%2C%20ideas%20and%20themes%20dominating%20the%20conversation%20in%20India%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fskodali%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ESrinivas%20Kodali%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20researcher%20on%20digitisation%20and%20a%20hacktivist.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703046642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20093656%2Ftablet-314153_1280.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ftelecommunications-bill-lays-the-ground-for-totalitarian-control-of-the-internet%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20Bill%20is%20being%20praised%20by%20the%20telecom%20industry%20for%20replacing%20archaic%20colonial%20laws%2C%20the%20Telecommunication%20Bill%202023%20is%20expected%20to%20provide%20a%20larger%20control%20than%20these%20colonial%20laws%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20its%20institutions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ftelecommunications-bill-lays-the-ground-for-totalitarian-control-of-the-internet%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Immigration%20fuels%20uptick%20in%20US%20population%20growth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703046364000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106141902%2Cimgsize-64008.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fimmigration-fuels-uptick-in-us-population-growth%2Farticleshow%2F106141859.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106141859.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Census%20Bureau%20released%20estimates%20showing%20that%20immigration%20has%20driven%20the%20highest%20population%20growth%20in%20two%20decades.%20The%20United%20States%20added%201.6%20million%20people%2C%20with%20over%20two-thirds%20of%