e%20last%20and%20be%20stored%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20perfume%20lasts%20up%20to%20five%20years.%20It%20expires%20much%20faster%20if%20not%20stored%20in%20a%20cool%20place%20as%20it%20is%20very%20sensitive%20to%20sunlight%20or%20air%20if%20left%20open%20without%20the%20cap%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20there%20a%20best%20time%20to%20apply%20perfume%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20time%20to%20apply%20perfume%20is%20right%20after%20the%20shower%20before%20getting%20dressed%20on%20the%20chest%20area%2C%20shoulders%2C%20and%20one%20wrist.%20This%20application%20should%20be%20done%20at%20about%2010%20inches%20away.%20The%20spray%20of%20the%20wrist%20is%20a%20good%20tip.%20Once%20dressed%2C%20keep%20the%20five%20spray%20routines%3B%20three%20on%20the%20skin%2C%20two%20on%20your%20clothes.%20One%20behind%20each%20ear%2C%20one%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20neck%2C%20one%20on%20your%20front%20left%20shoulder%2C%20and%20one%20on%20your%20back%20right%20shoulder.%20Only%20Eau%20fraiche%20or%20Eau%20de%20cologne%20should%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20pulse%20points%20of%20the%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20there%20a%20right%20way%20to%20try%20on%20perfume%20in%20order%20to%20make%20a%20decision%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20best%20to%20test%20a%20fragrance%20on%20your%20skin.%20The%20only%20issue%20is%20that%20you%20can%20only%20test%20one%20scent%20at%20a%20time.%20I%20like%20to%20start%20with%20a%20blotter%20strip%20or%20card.%20Spray%20twice%20downwards%2C%20pass%20the%20blotter%20strip%20through%20the%20fragrance%20cloud%2C%20wave%20under%20your%20nose%2C%20and%20inhale.%20Then%2C%20I%20move%20on%20to%20the%20skin%20test.%20Wash%20your%20hands%20earlier%2C%20not%20just%20before%20testing%20fragrances%2C%20and%20do%20not%20apply%20any%20hand%20cream.%20Spray%20onto%20the%20back%20of%20your%20hand%20from%20a%20distance%20of%20four%20to%20six%20inches%2C%20and%20no%20more%20than%2010%20inches%20depending%20on%20the%20atomizer%20pump.%20Start%20with%20just%20two%20sprays