s%20the%20second%20conversation%20that%20Modi%20had%20with%20Netanyahu%20since%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20terror%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20massive%20retaliation%20to%20the%20attack%20has%20killed%20thousands%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1737096926917775782%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20(December%2019)%20evening%2C%20Modi%20wrote%20that%20during%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproductive%E2%80%9D%20exchange%20of%20views%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Congoing%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%E2%80%9D%20with%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20two%20had%20%E2%80%9Cshared%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20about%20maritime%20traffic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20disruption%20of%20shipping%20lanes%20after%20Yemen-based%20Houthis%20attacked%20commercial%20vessels%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20to%20protest%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20strikes%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20post%20did%20not%20delve%20into%20specifics%2C%20the%20Israeli%20PM%E2%80%99s%20office%20alleged%20that%20the%20Houthis%E2%80%99%20attacks%20were%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FIsraeliPM%2Fstatus%2F1737100564238840259%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einstigated%20by%20Iran%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20also%20claimed%20that%20Modi%20%E2%80%9Cnoted%20that%20%5Bthe%5D%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20is%20an%20essential%20global%20necessity%20that%20must%20be%20ensured%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20Indian%20PM%20stated%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Chighlighted%20India%E2%80%99s%20consistent%20stand%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20early%20restoration%20of%20peace%20%5Band%5D%20stability%20in%20the%20region%20with%20continued%20humanitarian%20assistance%20for%20the%20affected%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20post%20did%20not%20repeat%20it%2C%20but%20India%20has%20until%20now%20referred%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attack%20as%20an%20act%20of%20terror%20and%20reiterated%20the%20need%20to%20combat%20terrorism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20had%20immediately%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20on%20October%207%2C%20which%20he%20reiterated%20in%20a%20phone%20conversation%20with%20Netanyahu%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20abstained%20from%20the%20first%20resolution%20of%20the%20193-member%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20(UNGA)%20on%20October%2026%20that%20called%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20to%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20its%20language%20did%20not%20refer%20to%20the%20October%207%20attack.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-votes-in-favour-of-unga-resolution-calling-for-immediate-ceasefire-in-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eless%20than%20two%20months%20later%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20India%20voted%20yes%20on%20a%20second%20resolution%20at%20the%20UNGA%20that%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20despite%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20condemnatory%20mention%20of%20Hamas%20in%20the%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20neither%20leader%20referred%20to%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20in%20their%20posts%2C%20Netanyahu%20thanked%20Modi%20for%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20support%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20just%20war%20to%20eliminate%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organization%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Israeli%20PM%20also%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20leaders%20also%20discussed%20advancing%20the%20arrival%20of%20foreign%20workers%20from%20India%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20clarification%20on%20this%20matter%20or%20its%20details%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20Indian%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fisrael-india-ink-agreement-to-allow-42-000-indian-workers-to-work-in-jewish-state-11683642390148.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20May%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20India%20and%20Israel%20had%20signed%20an%20agreement%20during%20the%20visit%20of%20Israeli%20foreign%20minister%20Eli%20Cohen%20that%20would%20facilitate%20arrangements%20for%2042%2C000%20Indian%20additional%20workers%20to%20reach%20Israel%2C%20out%20of%20which%2034%2C000%20would%20be%20brought%20into%20the%20construction%20industry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20currently%20around%2018%2C000%20to%2020%2C000%20Indian%20nationals%20in%20Israel%2C%20most%20of%20them%20working%20in%20the%20healthcare%20sector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20has%20been%20facing%20a%20perennial%20shortage%20of%20labour%20and%20has%20sought%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fisrael-construction-labour-shortage-india-china%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebring%20in%20more%20workers%20from%20India%2C%20China%20and%20Morocco.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20work%20permits%20of%20Palestinians%20cancelled%20after%20the%20October%207%20attack%2C%20the%20labour%20shortage%20had%20become%20even%20more%20acute%20and%20the%20Israeli%20housing%20industry%20called%20for%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fisraeli-construction-sector-moves-to-replace-palestinian-employees-with-indian-workers%2F7338259.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eearly%20arrival%20of%20Indian%20workers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-faces-manpower-shortage-in-construction-sector-looks-to-india-to-replace-palestinian-workers%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20diplomatic%20sources%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20preliminary%20talks%20were%20underway%20last%20month%20to%20bring%20around%2015%2C000%20Indian%20workers%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20spokesperson%20had%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20there%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37250%2FTranscript_of_Weekly_Media_Briefing_by_the_Official_Spokesperson_November_09_2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eno%20specific%20requests%20from%20Israel%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20reiterated%20in%20an%20answer%20by%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20External%20Affairs%20V.%20Muraleedharan%20in%20parliament%20on%20December%2014.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20has%20not%20made%20any%20discussions%20with%20Israel%20regarding%20possible%20replacement%20of%20Palestinian%20labourers%20with%20Indian%20workers%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Frajya-sabha.htm%3Fdtl%2F37408%2FQUESTION%2BNO1329%2BDEPLOYMENT%2BOF%2BINDIAN%2BWORKERS%2BIN%2BISRAEL%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20said%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20terror%20attacks%20in%20Israel%2C%20around%201%2C309%20Indian%20nationals%20returned%20to%20India%20in%20six%20special%20flights.%20While%20around%2011%20Indian%20nationals%20were%20in%20Palestine%2C%20only%20one%20has%20returned%20after%20being%20facilitated%20to%20escape%20Gaza%20through%20Egypt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703009947000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F14143039%2F2018_1-14-Benjamin-Netanyahu-and-Narendra-Modi26231292_10159929705395165_4506447465273333604_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2