his%20predecessor%2C%20K.%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20(KCR)%2C%20who%20was%20accused%20of%20being%20inaccessible.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20occupy%20the%20palatial%20official%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20bungalow%2C%20his%20decision%20to%20throw%20open%20the%20state%20secretariat%20to%20common%20people%2C%20his%20decision%20to%20re-institute%20Praja%20Darbar%20(a%20grievance%20redressal%20mechanism)%2C%20and%20his%20austerity%20measures%20have%20won%20him%20praise%20from%20several%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20refused%20to%20let%20the%20police%20purchase%20new%20high-end%20cars%20for%20his%20convoy%20%E2%80%93%20a%20practice%20familiar%20whenever%20the%20government%20or%20chief%20minister%20changes.%20He%20not%20only%20retained%20the%20old%20cars%20(used%20by%20his%20predecessors)%20but%20pruned%20their%20number%20from%2015%20to%20nine.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20agreed%20to%20give%20the%20cars%20fresh%20paint%20in%20a%20different%20colour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftelangana-revanth-reddy-fortified-pragati-bhavan-open-to-public%5C%22%3ETelangana%3A%20As%20Revanth%20Takes%20Over%2C%20Once-Fortified%20Official%20Residence%20of%20CM%20Thrown%20Open%20to%20Public%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)-led%20opposition%20has%20denied%20any%20refreshing%20style%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%20or%20the%20new%20government%20led%20by%20the%20Congress%20party.%20Former%20finance%20minister%20and%20BRS%20MLA%20T.%20Harish%20Rao%20said%20Reddy%20still%20spoke%20like%20an%20opposition%20leader%20rather%20than%20as%20a%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERao%20asked%20Reddy%20to%20prove%20his%20credentials%20as%20chief%20minister%2C%20instead%20of%20blaming%20the%20previous%20government%20all%20the%20time.%20According%20to%20Rao%2C%20Reddy%20relies%20on%20%E2%80%9Cfake%20news%E2%80%9D%20circulated%20on%20social%20media.%20He%20also%20alleged%20that%20Reddy%20on%20the%20very%20second%20day%20of%20assuming%20office%20had%20unleashed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20campaign%E2%80%9D%20on%20social%20media%20noting%20that%20he%20inherited%20huge%20debt%20from%20the%20previous%20BRS%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20taking%20oath%20as%20chief%20minister%20on%20December%207%2C%20Reddy%20handed%20over%20an%20appointment%20letter%20to%20T.%20Rajini%20on%20the%20same%20stage%20at%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Stadium%20in%20Hyderabad.%20A%20post-graduate%20in%20commerce%20from%20Osmania%20University%2C%20Rajini%20impressed%20Reddy%20with%20her%20articulation%20when%20she%20met%20him%20at%20the%20Congress%20party%20office%20three%20months%20ago.%20He%20had%20assured%20her%20that%20he%20would%20sign%20her%20appointment%20letter%20as%20the%20first%20file%20immediately%20after%20taking%20over%20as%20chief%20minister.%20Rajini%20has%20been%20appointed%20as%20a%20project%20manager%20in%20Telangana%20State%20Seed%20and%20Organic%20Certification%20Agency%20with%20a%20monthly%20salary%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%2C%20but%20on%20a%20contract%20basis%20until%20her%20service%20is%20regularised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19175635%2FGAwjl8VWkAEFtit.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19175635%2FGAwjl8VWkAEFtit.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19175635%2FGAwjl8VWkAEFtit-300x167.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19175635%2FGAwjl8VWkAEFtit-1024x570.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689881%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22668%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20signs%20the%20appointment%20letter%20of%20Rajini.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40TelanganaCMO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReddy%20came%20in%20for%20praise%20even%20in%20official%20circles%20for%20displaying%20%E2%80%9Cmaturity%E2%80%9D%20than%20previous%20chief%20ministers%20though%20he%20was%20not%20even%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20past.%20He%20began%20his%20political%20career%20as%20a%20territorial%20constituency%20member%20of%20a%20local%20body%2C%20served%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20legislative%20council%20(MLC)%20for%20a%20brief%2C%20and%20MLA%20twice.%20In%20his%20second%20term%20as%20MLA%2C%20he%20was%20often%20suspended%20from%20the%20Assembly%20or%20shouted%20down%20by%20treasury%20benches%20representing%20BRS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20also%20winning%20praise%20for%20handling%20legislative%20debates%20in%20the%20face%20of%20scathing%20attacks%20from%20BRS%20legislators.%20In%20the%20nearly%20two-hour%20speech%20that%20was%20live%20telecast%20as%20part%20of%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20motion%20of%20thanks%20to%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20address%2C%20he%20said%20his%20narrative%20was%20as%20good%20as%20punishment%20to%20the%20BRS%20leaders%20for%20their%20wrongdoing.%20He%20said%20his%20government%20would%20not%20press%20for%20their%20suspension%20for%20their%20unruly%20behaviour%20but%20would%20force%20them%20to%20listen%20to%20him%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20he%20dug%20into%20the%20sale%20of%20paddy%20seed%20grown%20by%20KCR%20in%20his%20150%20acres%20of%20crop%20to%20seed%20companies%20at%20Rs%204%2C250%20a%20quintal%20while%20other%20farmers%20got%20only%20Rs%201%2C900%20a%20quintal.%20He%20walked%20away%20with%20the%20credit%20of%20implementing%20two%20of%20the%20six%20guarantees%20of%20Congress%20immediately%20after%20taking%20over.%20They%20relate%20to%20free%20bus%20travel%20for%20women%20and%20a%20hike%20in%20the%20ceiling%20of%20cashless%20treatment%20under%20the%20Aarogyasri%20scheme%20for%20the%20poor%20in%20corporate%20hospitals%20from%20Rs%205%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarish%20Rao%2C%20however%2C%20claimed%20that%20it%20was%20not%20six%20but%2013%20guarantees%20which%20Congress%20gave%20and%20only%20two%20were%20delivered.%20Rao%20said%20the%20guarantee%20on%20health%20was%20not%20new%20because%20the%20previous%20BRS%20government%20had%20permitted%20organ%20transplants%20costing%20up%20to%20Rs%2011%20lakh%20for%20the%20poor%20at%20private%20hospitals%20for%20the%20last%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReddy%20ordered%20the%20removal%20of%20barricades%20at%20the%20premises%20hitherto%20occupied%20by%20KCR%20to%20make%20it%20accessible%20to%20the%20public%20for%20giving%20representations%20on%20public%20grievances%20redressal%20days.%20He%20has%20announced%20a%20judicial%20inquiry%20into%20question%20papers%20leak%20in%20recruitment%20exams%20and%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Kaleswaram%20lift-irrigation%20project%20which%20was%20hit%20by%20the%20sinking%20of%20a%20pier%20of%20one%20of%20its%20three%20barrages.%20He%20has%20also%20stopped%20the%20extension%20of%20Hyderabad%20metro%20rail%20works%20from%20Raidurg%20to%20the%20international%20airport%20following%20complaints%20that%20the%20work%20was%20commissioned%20to%20benefit%20a%20few%20landowners%20with%20close%20links%20in%20the%20previous%20BRS%20government.%20Instead%2C%20the%20route%20was%20ordered%20to%20be%20realigned%20from%20the%20Old%20City%20to%20the%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20was%20firm%20on%20the%20replacement%20of%20the%20Dharani%20portal%20of%20land%20transactions%20which%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20BRS%20government%20three%20years%20ago.%20This%20was%20because%20of%20lakhs%20of%20complaints%20by%20the%20public%20about%20illegal%20transactions%20that%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20eased%20out%20a%20dozen%20retired%20bureaucrats%20who%20were%20employed%20as%20advisors%20to%20the%20government%20and%20effected%20major%20changes%20in%20the%20top%20brass%20of%20IAS%20and%20IPS.%20He%20also%20stripped%20the%20chairpersons%20of%20a%20dozen%20corporations%20of%20their%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20wanted%20a%20delegation%20to%20visit%20Bengaluru%20to%20discuss%20the%20release%20of%20water%20by%20Karnataka%20from%20the%20Narayanpur%20dam%20to%20meet%20the%20drinking%20water%20requirement%20of%20Telangana%20in%20the%20Krishna%20basin.%20He%20strengthened%20the%20Telangana%20State%20Anti-Narcotics%20Bureau%20by%20appointing%20a%20full-time%20director%20and%20sanctioning%20300%20staff%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20a%20meeting%20with%20former%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20governor%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20to%20discuss%20measures%20to%20put%20the%20economy%20of%20the%20state%20back%20on%20the%20rails%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20outstanding%20loans%20touching%20Rs%203.66%20lakh%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20department%20was%20asked%20to%20prepare%20a%20White%20Paper%20on%20the%20economy%20to%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20assembly%20on%20Wednesday.%20On%20his%20instructions%2C%20the%20government%20machinery%20is%20gearing%20up%20to%20resume%20distribution%20of%20ration%20cards%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20inclusion%20of%20new%20names%20at%20gram%20sabhas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20analyst%20K.%20Nageshwar%20said%20the%20optics%20of%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20government%20have%20been%20fairly%20good%20so%20far.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20opening%20the%20gates%20of%20the%20Secretariat%20to%20the%20public%2C%20holding%20Praja%20Darbar%20to%20hear%20public%20grievances%2C%20and%20resuming%20permissions%20for%20protests%20at%20Dharna%20Chowk%20near%20Indira%20Park%2C%20Reddy%20has%20shown%20his%20liberal%20and%20democratic%20approach%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Nageshwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20Jana%20Samithi%20chief%20M.%20Kodandaram%20said%20the%20days%20of%20%E2%80%9Cwarm%20and%20friendly%20governments%E2%80%9D%20are%20back%20under%20Reddy.%20Kodandaram%20is%20set%20to%20assume%20a%20key%20role%20as%20an%20interface%20between%20the%20government%20and%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702992564000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19174512%2FEffect-34.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-revanth-reddy-optics-accessible-chief-minister%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20chief%20minister's%20refusal%20to%20occupy%20the%20official%20bungalow%2C%20his%20decision%20to%20throw%20open%20the%20state%20secretariat%20to%20common%20people%2C%20his%20decision%20to%20re-institute%20Praja%20Darbar%2C%20and%20his%20austerity%20measures%20have%20won%20praise%20from%20several%20quarters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-revanth-reddy-optics-accessible-chief-minister%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Influencer%20apologises%20after%20misleading%20fans%20with%20sale%20of%20'charity'%20Christmas%20cake%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702991880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-italian-chiara-ferragni_6398045.jpg%3F20231219140759%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fchiara-ferragni-apologises-after-misleading-fans-with-sale-of-charity-christmas-cake-13034084%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Italian%20fashion%20influencer%20Chiara%20Ferragni%20has%20apologised%20after%20misleading%20her%20followers%20over%20sales%20of%20a%20Christmas%20cake%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A120%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fchiara-ferragni-apologises-after-misleading-fans-with-sale-of-charity-christmas-cake-13034084%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fchiara-ferragni-apologises-after-misleading-fans-with-sale-of-charity-christmas-cake-13034084%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fchiara-ferragni-apologises-after-misleading-fans-with-sale-of-charity-christmas-cake-13034084%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Illusory%20or%20Real%3F%20Unpacking%20the%20Recent%20Increase%20in%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fillusory-or-real-unpacking-the-recent-increase-in-womens-labour-force-participation-in-india%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3ECEDA.%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(for%20those%20aged%2015-59)%20has%20seen%20a%20growth%20from%2051.5%25%20to%2058.3%25%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-23.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20growth%20has%20been%20on%20account%20of%20improvement%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20improvement%20in%20the%20initial%20years%20can%20be%20partially%20explained%20by%20a%20change%20in%20measurement.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20sustained%20increase%20reflects%20an%20increase%20in%20women%20in%20self-employment%2C%20which%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20paid%20work%20and%20disguised%20unemployment.%20There%20is%2C%20however%2C%20no%20increase%20in%20job%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Economic%20Forum%E2%80%99s%20Global%20Gender%20Gap%20Report%20for%202022%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fworld%2Fis-saudi-arabia-doing-better-than-india-in-bridging-gender-gap-wef-report-says-yes%2F1036026%2F%5C%22%3Ejaws%20to%20drop%20and%20eyes%20to%20pop%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20put%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20where%20gender%20gaps%20are%20mandated%20by%20law%2C%20ahead%20of%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2022.pdf%5C%22%3Erespective%20rankings%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20gender%20gap%20index.%20In%20the%20following%20year%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2022.pdf%5C%22%3EIndia%20did%20manage%20to%20outrank%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20West%20Asian%20counterpart%20marginally%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20rank%20fairly%20low%20%E2%80%93%20127%20among%20146%20countries.%20The%20index%20measures%20gaps%20on%20four%20broad%20parameters%20(also%20called%20sub-indices)%20%E2%80%93%20economic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%2C%20educational%20attainment%2C%20health%20and%20survival%2C%20and%20political%20empowerment.%20India%E2%80%99s%20poor%20scoring%20on%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%E2%80%9D%20for%20women%20contributed%20substantially%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fgender-gap-report-21-indias-ranking-continues-to-slide%2F%5C%22%3Epersistently%20low%20rank%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20global%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20participation%20and%20opportunities%E2%80%9D%20relates%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20The%20issue%20of%20low%20and%20declining%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(FLFPR)%20in%20India%20has%20been%20extensively%20discussed%20both%20on%20CEDA%20pages%20(see%20examples%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fcovid-19-income-shocks-and-female-employment%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecline-in-female-labour-force-participation-be-cautious-how-you-interpret-it%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fpicture-this-if-indian-states-were-countries-female-lfpr%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%20as%20well%20as%20by%20CEDA%20researchers%2C%20who%20have%20analysed%20some%20key%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X2300253X%5C%22%3Ecauses%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.iza.org%2Fdp14639.pdf%5C%22%3Epatterns%20showing%20that%20women%20work%20when%20work%20is%20available%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iza.org%2Fpublications%2Fdp%2F14497%2Fwords-matter-gender-jobs-and-applicant-behavior%5C%22%3Eremedies%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20rigorous%20empirical%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20data%20from%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Surveys%20(PLFS)%20since%202017-18%20provides%20more%20than%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20as%20it%20reveals%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20overall%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(LFPR)%20by%20the%20current%20weekly%20status%20(or%20CWS%2C%20where%20the%20reference%20period%20is%20one%20week)%20of%20those%20aged%2015-59%20from%2051.5%25%20to%2058.3%25%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-23%20(Figure%201).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20is%20driven%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20FLFPRs%20from%2022.9%25%20to%2034.1%25%20over%20the%20period.%20If%20this%20is%20indeed%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20trend%2C%20it%20is%20undoubtedly%20heartening%20and%20very%20welcome.%20PLFS%20also%20provides%20data%20for%20participation%20rates%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdge.gov.in%2Fdge%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FAnnual_Report_PLFS_2022-23.pdf%5C%22%3Eusual%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20(principal%20and%20subsidiary%20status)%20with%20a%20reference%20period%20of%20one%20year.%20Here%20we%20report%20figures%20from%20CWS%2C%20but%20the%20usual%20status%20trends%20are%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630.png%201152w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630-300x184.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19164937%2Fimage-1630-1024x628.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689853%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22707%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure1.html%5C%22%3EFigure%201%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrue%20to%20historical%20patterns%2C%20the%20urban%20FLFPR%20continues%20to%20be%20lower%20than%20rural%2C%20but%20both%20show%20an%20increase%3A%205%20percentage%20points%20for%20urban%20and%2014%20percentage%20points%20for%20rural%20women.%20The%20pattern%20of%20increase%20in%20rural%20women%E2%80%99s%20LFPRs%20shows%20two%20big%20spikes%20of%20roughly%206%20percentage%20points%20each%3A%20one%20between%202018-19%20and%202019-20%20and%20the%20second%20between%202021-22%20and%202022-23.%20The%20corresponding%20urban%20increase%20was%20around%202%20percentage%20points%20in%20both%20instances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20useful%20to%20remind%20ourselves%20of%20the%20trends%20in%20LFPRs%20prior%20to%202017-18.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20FLFPR%20declined%20from%2039.7%25%20in%202004-05%20to%2028.9%25%20in%202011-12%2C%20to%20a%20further%2022.9%25%20in%202017-18%20(Figure%202).%20The%20Indian%20government%20started%20using%20the%20PLFS%20only%20in%202017-18.%20Prior%20to%20that%2C%20the%20quinquennial%20Employment-Unemployment%20Surveys%20(EUS)%20were%20used%20to%20measure%20the%20employment%20situation%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20EUS%20was%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20(NSS)%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20(MoSPI)%2C%20the%20same%20ministry%20that%20now%20conducts%20PLFS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631-300x182.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165102%2Fimage-1631-1024x622.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689854%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure2.html%5C%22%3EFigure%202%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20increase%20in%20FLFPRs%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20the%20increase%20in%20rural%20women%E2%80%99s%20increased%20participation%2C%20just%20as%20the%20decline%20was%20due%20to%20a%20drop%20in%20rural%20FLFPR.%20Let%20us%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20increase%20using%20the%20same%20set%20of%20arguments%20that%20have%20so%20far%20been%20deployed%20to%20analyse%20the%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20a%20norms%20story%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20historically%20low%20level%20as%20well%20as%20the%20decline%20in%20female%20LFPRs%20have%20been%20widely%20attributed%20to%20conservative%20social%20norms%2C%20both%20by%20academics%20as%20well%20as%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unfpa.org%2Fpublications%2Fmanual-social-norms-and-change-2022%5C%22%3Emultilateral%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20crux%20of%20this%20argument%20is%20that%20women%20are%20not%20allowed%20by%20their%20families%20and%20by%20the%20local%20community%20to%20participate%20in%20paid%20work%2C%20a%20norm%20that%20women%20themselves%20largely%20internalise.%20If%20this%20argument%20is%20true%2C%20the%20latest%20increase%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20FLFPR%20is%20a%20puzzle.%20Did%20norms%20governing%20Indian%20women%20(assuming%20incorrectly%20in%20the%20first%20place%20that%20there%20is%20a%20common%20set%20of%20norms%20applicable%20across%20castes%20and%20communities)%20suddenly%20and%20inexplicably%20loosen%20over%20the%20last%20six%20years%2C%20in%20two%20bouts%3F%20That%20seems%20highly%20unlikely.%20There%20is%20no%20complementary%20evidence%20from%20any%20other%20source%20that%20hints%20at%20this%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20a%20measurement%20story%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20might%20wonder%20about%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20recent%20data%2C%20and%20indeed%20there%20is%20much%20to%20say%20about%20measurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work.%20Does%20the%20recent%20increase%20reflect%20a%20changed%20way%20of%20measuring%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3F%20When%20the%20EUS%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20annual%20PLFS%2C%20there%20were%20some%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20sampling%20design%20and%20interview%20schedules.%20Readers%20interested%20in%20the%20full%20set%20of%20changes%20can%20refer%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdge.gov.in%2Fdge%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-11%2FAnnual_Report_PLFS_2017-18.pdf%5C%22%3Ethis%20document%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20know%2C%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20measure%20both%20participation%20in%20economic%20work%20as%20well%20as%20availability%20for%20economic%20work.%20International%20standards%20count%20economic%20work%20as%20employment%20for%20pay%20or%20profit%3B%20by%20this%20standard%2C%20an%20unpaid%20helper%20would%20not%20be%20counted%20as%20being%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20However%2C%20in%20developing%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20there%20is%20a%20large%20number%20of%20workers%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20who%20are%20involved%20in%20economic%20work%2C%20i.e.%2C%20in%20the%20production%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20that%20get%20counted%20in%20GDP%20but%20are%20not%20paid%20for%20that%20work.%20Women%20in%20unpaid%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eeconomic%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0work%20tend%20to%20fall%20through%20the%20cracks%20of%20the%20statistical%20system%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Fvisible-and-invisible-barriers-women-working-india%5C%22%3Enot%20get%20counted%20as%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20be%20absolutely%20sure%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20among%20the%20new%20features%20of%20PLFS%2C%20two%20might%20have%20contributed%20to%20better%20measurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3A%20one%2C%20for%20each%20day%20of%20the%20reference%20week%2C%20PLFS%20collected%20hours%20worked%20in%20each%20economic%20activity.%20Second%2C%20for%20those%20who%20were%20available%20for%20additional%20economic%20work%20in%20the%20reference%20week%2C%20information%20on%20hours%20available%20for%20each%20day%20of%20the%20reference%20week%20was%20collected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20extent%20this%20is%20a%20measurement%20story%2C%20we%20could%20argue%20that%20the%20earlier%20low%20proportions%20reflected%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X2300253X%5C%22%3Emismeasurement%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20the%20recent%20increase%20reflects%20improved%20measurement.%20However%2C%20this%20would%20explain%20only%20the%20initial%20increase%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20PLFS%20rounds.%20It%20cannot%20explain%20the%20steady%20increase%20over%20six%20years.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20each%20year%20is%20more%20accurate%20than%20the%20previous%20year.%20Instead%2C%20it%20suggests%20a%20genuine%20increase%20in%20women%20entering%20productive%20work.%20But%20is%20this%20coming%20from%20an%20increase%20in%20jobs%20for%20women%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20about%20more%20jobs%20in%20rural%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20recent%20increase%20in%20FLFPR%20could%20not%20be%20due%20to%20a%20sudden%20increase%20in%20work%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20as%20we%20do%20not%20observe%20any%20corresponding%20spikes%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20of%20rural%20men.%20As%20Figure%203%20shows%20that%20the%20increase%20is%20driven%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20rural%20women%20under%20the%20broad%20category%20of%20%E2%80%9Cself-employed%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20has%20risen%20from%2055.9%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2070.1%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632-300x180.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19165405%2Fimage-1632-1024x613.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689855%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure3.html%5C%22%3EFigure%203%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20self-employment%20encompass%3F%20In%20brief%2C%20it%20includes%20any%20activity%20where%20one%20is%20not%20working%20for%20an%20employer.%20It%20could%20include%20the%20largest%20entrepreneurs%20as%20well%20as%20a%20farmer%2C%20the%20neighbourhood%20cobbler%20or%20the%20vegetable%20seller%20on%20a%20cart.%20For%20those%20not%20in%20wage%20or%20casual%20work%2C%20participation%20in%20agriculture%20and%20allied%20activities%20counts%20as%20self-employment.%20The%20PLFS%20further%20categorises%20those%20who%20are%20self-employed%20into%20three%20categories%3A%20%E2%80%9Cemployer%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cown-account%20worker%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cunpaid%20helper%E2%80%9D.%20Own-account%20workers%20are%20one-person%20enterprises%20and%20unpaid%20helpers%20typically%20are%20individuals%20working%20on%20family%20enterprises%20but%20not%20being%20paid%20for%20their%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20spike%20in%20FLFPR%20between%202018-19%20and%202019-20%2C%20it%20was%20the%20proportion%20of%20unpaid%20helpers%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ewithin%3C%2Fi%3E%20self-employed%20that%20increased%20(from%2033.1%25%20to%2038.4%25)%2C%20while%20the%20proportions%20of%20self-employed%20that%20were%20own-account%20workers%20declined%20from%2022.9%25%20to%2020.9%25.%20The%20proportion%20of%20rural%20women%20workers%20who%20worked%20as%20regular%20salaried%20workers%20also%20declined%20from%2013.4%25%20to%2010.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20spike%2C%20more%20recently%2C%20between%202021-22%20and%202022-23%2C%20it%20was%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20working%20as%20own-account%20workers%20that%20increased%2C%20whereas%20the%20proportion%20as%20unpaid%20workers%20remained%20stable%20at%20roughly%2038%25.%20Thus%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20female%20LFPRs%20is%20attributable%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20proportions%20of%20women%20working%20as%20own-account%20enterprises%20or%20as%20unpaid%20helpers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20we%20see%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20share%20of%20rural%20women%20working%20as%20casual%20labour%20(from%2031.3%25%20to%2019.6%25)%20and%20no%20change%20in%20the%20proportion%20working%20in%20regular%20wage%20or%20salaried%20jobs%20(roughly%2010%25).%20If%20job%20availability%20in%20rural%20areas%20had%20increased%2C%20we%20would%20have%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20both%20these%20proportions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormally%20a%20shift%20from%20casual%20labour%20to%20regular%20wage%20labour%20signals%20an%20improvement%20in%20work%20conditions.%20However%2C%20Indian%20data%20does%20not%20show%20this%20shift.%20It%20appears%20that%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20as%20casual%20labour%20is%20being%20more%20than%20compensated%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20two%20subsections%20of%20the%20self-employed%20category%3A%20unpaid%20helper%20and%20own%20account%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20this%20disguised%20unemployment%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202017-18%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%20share%20of%20men%20who%20were%20employed%20in%20the%20primary%20sector%20(agriculture%2C%20forestry%20and%20fishing)%20declined%20from%2037%25%20to%2033.4%25.%20However%2C%20for%20women%2C%20this%20share%20went%20up%20from%2052.8%25%20to%2058.8%25%20(Figure%204).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633-300x178.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170130%2Fimage-1633-1024x608.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689858%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22713%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure4.html%5C%22%3EFigure%204%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3EMost%20of%20the%20growth%20in%20the%20share%20of%20self-employed%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20of%20those%20working%20as%20own-account%20workers%20has%20also%20been%20in%20this%20sector%20in%20this%20period.%20Figure%205%20shows%20the%20change%20over%20time%20in%20proportion%20of%20men%20and%20women%20across%20broad%20sectors%20and%20by%20type%20of%20employment%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFocusing%20on%20rural%20women%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20who%20are%20self-employed%20in%20agriculture%2C%20from%2063.7%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2079.1%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20roughly%2015%20percentage%20points.%20There%20has%20also%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20self-employed%20rural%20women%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20services%2C%20though%20the%20quantum%20of%20increase%20is%20smaller%3A%2010%20percentage%20points%20for%20manufacturing%2C%20from%2071.7%25%20to%2081.8%25%2C%20and%20six%20percentage%20points%20for%20services%20from%2023.1%25%20to%2029.1%25%20(even%20as%20the%20share%20of%20women%20working%20in%20manufacturing%20has%20only%20increased%20marginally%20while%20those%20working%20in%20services%20has%20seen%20a%20small%20decline).%20Thus%2C%20self-employment%20among%20rural%20women%20has%20occurred%20across%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170623%2Fimage-1636.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170623%2Fimage-1636.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170623%2Fimage-1636-300x111.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170623%2Fimage-1636-1024x377.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689862%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFigure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure5a.html%5C%22%3E5a%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure5b.html%5C%22%3E5b%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170913%2Fimage-1637.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170913%2Fimage-1637.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170913%2Fimage-1637-300x124.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19170913%2Fimage-1637-1024x424.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689863%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFigure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure5c.html%5C%22%3E5c%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F15122023%2Ffigure5d.html%5C%22%3E5d%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20increase%20in%20self-employment%20in%20agriculture%20for%20rural%20women%20is%20mirrored%20in%20the%20steady%20decline%20in%20the%20proportion%20working%20as%20casual%20labour%20in%20agriculture%2C%20with%20virtually%20no%20change%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20regular%20salaried%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20the%20decline%20in%20casual%20labour%20been%20reflected%20in%20an%20increase%20in%20regular%20salaried%20jobs%2C%20it%20would%20have%20indicated%20an%20improvement%20in%20job%20quality.%20However%2C%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case.%20The%20increase%20in%20self-employment%20in%20agriculture%20could%20reflect%20disguised%20unemployment%20or%20underemployment%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20too%20many%20workers%20are%20doing%20too%20few%20jobs.%20This%20essentially%20means%20that%20women%20are%20engaged%20in%20agriculture%20but%20not%20to%20their%20full%20productive%20capacity.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20pattern%20of%20earnings%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20self-employed%20women%20earning%20more%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%206%20shows%20gross%20earnings%20in%20constant%20prices%20from%20self-employment%20separately%20for%20four%20quarters%20for%20the%20six%20years%2C%20separately%20for%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20for%20male%20and%20female%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19171952%2Fimage-1638